class Solution {
public:
    int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses bitwise operations to count the set bits in the binary representation of n. It iteratively shifts n to the right and adds the least significant bit to the count. This approach has a high efficiency due to its constant time complexity and low space complexity.

